<figureCitation box="[1111,1234,1832,1859]" captionStart="Figures 10–16" captionStartId="8.[192,279,1799,1825]" captionTargetBox="[216,1416,213,1768]" captionTargetId="figure-18@8.[216,1416,213,1768]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Figures 10–16. Dyslexia belamyi Skelley and Gasca-Álvarez, holotype male, unless stated otherwise. 10) Dorsal habitus.11) Ventral habitus. 12) Lateral habitus. 13) Anterior dorsal oblique view of head and pronotum. 14) Anterior ventral oblique view of head and pronotum, not male protibial dimorphism. 15) Male genitalia. 16) Female genitalia, allotype." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5353888" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5353888/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">Fig. 10, 13</figureCitation>
); male with tibiae slightly but noticeable swollen in apical quarter (
<figureCitation box="[868,946,1866,1892]" captionStart="Figures 10–16" captionStartId="8.[192,279,1799,1825]" captionTargetBox="[216,1416,213,1768]" captionTargetId="figure-18@8.[216,1416,213,1768]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Figures 10–16. Dyslexia belamyi Skelley and Gasca-Álvarez, holotype male, unless stated otherwise. 10) Dorsal habitus.11) Ventral habitus. 12) Lateral habitus. 13) Anterior dorsal oblique view of head and pronotum. 14) Anterior ventral oblique view of head and pronotum, not male protibial dimorphism. 15) Male genitalia. 16) Female genitalia, allotype." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5353888" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5353888/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">Fig. 14</figureCitation>
), female tibiae slender entire length; 
<collectingCountry box="[1348,1442,1866,1892]" name="Ecuador" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
........................................ 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[850,1437,1900,1930]" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">
