, 
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1302,1437,1900,1926]" pageId="6" pageNumber="5" rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
— Antennomere XI pale white; head lacking black central spot on vertex (
<figureCitation box="[1106,1230,214,240]" captionStart="Figures 17‒23" captionStartId="10.[192,279,1686,1712]" captionTargetBox="[192,1440,213,1656]" captionTargetId="figure-56@10.[192,1440,213,1656]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Figures 17‒23. Dyslexia dathomirria Skelley and Gasca-Álvarez. 17) Dorsal habitus. 18) Ventral habitus. 19) Lateral habitus. 20) Anterior oblique view of head and pronotum. 21) ventral view head and prosternum. 22) Male genitalia. 23) Female genitalia, allotype." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5353892" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5353892/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">Fig. 17, 20</figureCitation>
); male and female tibiae slender entire length (
<figureCitation box="[648,727,248,274]" captionStart="Figures 17‒23" captionStartId="10.[192,279,1686,1712]" captionTargetBox="[192,1440,213,1656]" captionTargetId="figure-56@10.[192,1440,213,1656]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Figures 17‒23. Dyslexia dathomirria Skelley and Gasca-Álvarez. 17) Dorsal habitus. 18) Ventral habitus. 19) Lateral habitus. 20) Anterior oblique view of head and pronotum. 21) ventral view head and prosternum. 22) Male genitalia. 23) Female genitalia, allotype." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5353892" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5353892/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">Fig. 21</figureCitation>
